@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Xtrings" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your
Workbench must have at least 8 colours.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Xtrings runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga
      with a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, click on a loop that is located on the edge of the game
board, this will move all shapes that are in the row or column by
one position toward the clicked loop. If a shape or empty space was
located at the edge of the board, it will 'wrap around' to the
other edge.

  When a series of 4 shapes or more of the same type is in line
diagonally, these shapes are then eliminated and you get points
according to their number; 4 shapes give 1 point, 5 shapes give
4 points. If there are more shapes, the number of points will be
multiplied by 2 for each additional shape of the same type that
was eliminated (8, 16, 32, 64 points...). Note that the shapes of
the same type do not have to be in the *same* series, as the game
counts all shapes of the same type that have been simultaneously
eliminated...  But one important thing to remember is that if the
remaining number of shapes of the same type gets between 1 and 3,
the game will immediately end.

  As shapes are removed from the game board, they are not replaced.
When the board is empty, the game displays a new board with more
(up to 8) types of shapes.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

